## ReviewFlow Domain Context

Keep these domain facts in mind when assessing severity:

### Core Aggregates & Transaction Criticality

- **Submissions** — core aggregate. A submission involves: S3 upload (`uploadExecutor`), metadata persistence, and a status transition. These **must be atomic**. S3 upload is async (non-transactional by design); the DB side (metadata + status) must be one TX. Do not flag the S3 call being outside the TX — that is correct.
- **Grading** — grade record creation, submission status update, and notification dispatch. Partial completion corrupts academic records. Instructor-graded assessments (PRD-12) write to `instructor_scores` + update submission state — must be one TX.
- **JWT / Auth** — token issuance, refresh token persistence (`refresh_tokens`), family tracking (`refresh_token_families`, V33), session context (`session_contexts`, V33), and audit records must be co-transactional. Refresh rotation (V28) and device/IP context (V29) add more columns — all must commit or roll back together.
- **Grade Export (PRD-06)** — bulk read across `evaluations`, `rubric_scores`, `instructor_scores`. Isolation level and `readOnly = true` matter here.
- **File Preview (PRD-07)** — S3 pre-signed URL generation. Read-only; URL generation must not be inside a write TX.
- **Notifications / Announcements (PRD-03/04)** — email dispatched via `emailTaskExecutor` (`@Async("emailTaskExecutor")`), notifications via `notificationExecutor` (`@Async("notificationExecutor")`). These run outside the TX by design. **Do not flag them as RULE-05 violations** — the async executor pattern is intentional here. Only flag if a listener doing DB writes runs inside a still-open caller TX.
- **Extensions (PRD-05)** — extension approval writes to `extension_requests` AND must update the related submission deadline. Both writes must be one TX.
- **Discussions (PRD-17, V34)** — `discussions` + `discussion_posts` tables. Post creation, notification dedup column updates, and any status transitions must be atomic.
- **Messaging (PRD-18, V32)** — `conversations`, `conversation_participants`, `messages`, `message_attachments`. Message send + participant last-read update must be atomic.
- **Password Reset (V31)** — `password_reset_tokens` insert + invalidation of prior tokens for the same user must be one TX.
- **Lockout (V27)** — failed-attempt counter increment + lockout timestamp set on `users` must be atomic to prevent race conditions under concurrent login attempts.

### Async Executor Map (do not flag these as TX violations — they are intentional)

| Bean | Used by | Note |
|---|---|---|
| `notificationExecutor` | `NotificationEventListener` | `@Async("notificationExecutor")` — runs post-TX |
| `emailTaskExecutor` | `EmailEventListener` | `@Async("emailTaskExecutor")` — runs post-TX |
| `uploadExecutor` | S3 upload path | Intentionally non-transactional |
| `pdfExecutor` | `PdfGenerationListener` | Async PDF generation — intentionally non-transactional |
| `gradeAggregateExecutor` | `GradeAggregateUpdateListener` | Async aggregate recalculation |
| `csvWorkerExecutor` | CSV import validate/commit | Has its own TX management |

Flag RULE-05 only when a **non-listener, non-executor-aware** `@Transactional` method directly spawns work via `CompletableFuture.runAsync` or `executor.submit` that touches the DB.

### Known Active Issues (from `MASTER_PROJECT_SUMMARY.md §7`)

Be aware of these when scanning `SystemService`:
- `SystemService.collectAndPushMetrics()` uses stub/zero values for DB pool and cache metrics — not a TX boundary issue, but note if you see it in context.
- `SystemService.getCacheStats()` uses Caffeine `estimatedSize()` — also not a TX issue.

### What Is NOT in the Codebase (do not flag phantom violations)

- **OAuth (PRD-14)** — no OAuth controller, service, or `oauth_accounts` migration exists. Do not flag missing TX on non-existent code.
- **Content delivery (PRD-16)** — not implemented.
- **V30 migration** — intentionally skipped. Not a missing file to flag.

