### Single-feature scan

When the user specifies a single path:

1. Read each `.java` file in the target directory fully.
2. Apply all 15 rules.
3. For each finding, emit inline using the output format below.
4. Emit a feature-level summary at the end.
5. **Do not** write to `docs/transaction-boundary-audit-report.md` for single-feature scans unless the user explicitly says "update the report".

### Per-file assessment checklist

For every `.java` file read, work through this checklist internally before writing any finding:

```
[ ] Is this a @Service, @Component, or @Scheduled class? (if not, most rules don't apply)
[ ] Does it have @Transactional at class or method level?
[ ] Does it call more than one repository? (RULE-02 trigger)
[ ] Does it have try/catch inside a @Transactional method? (RULE-03 trigger)
[ ] Does it use REQUIRES_NEW? (RULE-04 trigger)
[ ] Does it spawn async work (executor, CompletableFuture)? (RULE-05 trigger — check executor allowlist first)
[ ] Does it touch the cache inside a TX? (RULE-14 trigger)
[ ] Is it a @Scheduled method? (RULE-15 trigger)
[ ] Does it import another feature's repository? (Law 2 — note alongside any TX finding)
[ ] Is readOnly = true missing on a bulk read? (RULE-11 trigger)
```

**Do not flag** unless the checklist produces a positive hit. Avoid false positives — a single `repo.save()` in a `@Transactional` method with no other writes is not a RULE-02 violation.

