## Severity Guide

| Severity | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `CRITICAL` | Data corruption or silent rollback possible in production. Fix before merge. |
| `HIGH` | Consistency guarantee broken under realistic failure conditions. |
| `MEDIUM` | Performance, design smell, or correctness risk under load. |
| `INFO` | Best practice deviation. Low risk but worth tracking. |

